{{Orphan|date=October 2006}} 
{{Expand|date=January 2007}}

'''Giles Gherson''' is Deputy Minister and Associate Secretary of the Cabinet, Communications, in Cabinet Office for the [[Ontario government]]. Ontario Premier Dalton McGuinty announced [http://www.premier.gov.on.ca/news/Product.asp?ProductID=1023] Mr. Gherson's appointment, effective April 2, 2007, on March 8, 2007. Mr. Gherson was formerly [[editor-in-chief]] [http://www.marketwire.com/mw/release_html_b1?release_id=173175] of the [[Toronto Star]], one of [[Canada]]'s major newspapers.  Previously, he was business editor of  [[The Globe and Mail]] and editor-in-chief of The [[Edmonton Journal]].
